---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Mechanical Engineering · Virtual Labs · AquinTutor" description="Beam bending, stress-strain, trusses, Mohr's circle, gear trains, thermodynamic cycles and vibrations — computed live.">

<style>
  body { background: #0a0a0c; color: #e8e8ee; margin: 0; }
  .mz-wrap { max-width: 1360px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px 4vw 80px; }
  .mz-back { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; color: #9aa0a6; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .mz-back:hover { color: #67e8f9; }
  .mz-eye { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; }
  .mz-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 38px; font-weight: 600; margin: 4px 0 6px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1.1; }
  .mz-title em { color: #67e8f9; font-style: italic; font-weight: 500; }
  .mz-sub { color: #9aa0a6; max-width: 820px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.55; margin: 0 0 22px; }

  /* shell: experiment sidebar + workbench */
  .mz-shell { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 268px minmax(0,1fr); gap: 18px; }
  @media (max-width: 960px) { .mz-shell { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .mz-exp-list { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 10px; align-self: start; position: sticky; top: 14px; }
  .mz-exp-list h4 { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #fbbf24; font-weight: 700; margin: 6px 8px 10px; }
  .mz-exp { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 9px; width: 100%; text-align: left; background: transparent; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 8px; color: #cfd6da; font-family: inherit; padding: 9px 10px; cursor: pointer; margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .mz-exp:hover { background: #15171f; }
  .mz-exp.active { background: rgba(103,232,249,0.10); border-color: #67e8f9; }
  .mz-exp .num { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: #67e8f9; flex: 0 0 auto; width: 18px; }
  .mz-exp .nm { font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.3; }
  .mz-exp.active .nm { color: #fff; }

  .mz-bench { min-width: 0; }
  .mz-exp-head { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 26px; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 4px; color: #fff; }
  .mz-exp-tag { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 14px; }

  .mz-tabs { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 4px; margin-bottom: 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid #1d1d28; }
  .mz-tab { background: transparent; border: none; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; color: #9aa0a6; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10.5px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 9px 12px; cursor: pointer; }
  .mz-tab:hover { color: #cfd6da; }
  .mz-tab.active { color: #67e8f9; border-bottom-color: #67e8f9; }

  .mz-sec { display: none; }
  .mz-sec.active { display: block; }

  .mz-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 300px minmax(0,1fr); gap: 18px; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { .mz-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  .mz-panel { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .mz-panel h3 { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 12px; }

  .mz-ctl { display: grid; gap: 5px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .mz-ctl label { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #9aa6b6; font-weight: 700; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; }
  .mz-ctl label span { color: #67e8f9; }
  .mz-ctl input[type=range] { width: 100%; accent-color: #67e8f9; }
  .mz-ctl select { width: 100%; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; color: #fff; padding: 7px 10px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 12px; font-family: inherit; }

  .mz-seg { display: flex; gap: 6px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .mz-seg button { flex: 1; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; color: #9aa0a6; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 8px 6px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; }
  .mz-seg button.on { background: rgba(103,232,249,0.12); border-color: #67e8f9; color: #67e8f9; }

  .mz-metric { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto; gap: 8px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11.5px; padding: 5px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a25; }
  .mz-metric:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .mz-metric-l { color: #9aa6b6; }
  .mz-metric-v { color: #67e8f9; font-weight: 700; text-align: right; }
  .mz-metric-v.amber { color: #fbbf24; }
  .mz-metric-v.green { color: #86efac; }
  .mz-metric-v.red { color: #fca5a5; }
  .mz-metric-v.purple { color: #a78bfa; }

  .mz-svg { width: 100%; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 10px; display: block; }
  .mz-formula { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 12px; color: #cfd6da; line-height: 1.7; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #1d1d28; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px 14px; margin-top: 4px; }
  .mz-formula b { color: #fbbf24; }
  .mz-note { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 10px; color: #6b7280; line-height: 1.6; margin-top: 8px; }
  .mz-plots { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .mz-plots { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  /* text-content sections */
  .mz-prose { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px 22px; max-width: 900px; }
  .mz-prose p { color: #c5cbd2; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .mz-prose ol { color: #c5cbd2; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 22px; margin: 0; }
  .mz-prose ol li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .mz-prose .eqs { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.5px; color: #67e8f9; line-height: 1.9; background: #0a0a0c; border: 1px solid #1d1d28; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px; margin: 4px 0 16px; }
  .mz-prose .eqs b { color: #fbbf24; }
  .mz-prose .refs { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .mz-prose .refs li { font-size: 12.5px; color: #9aa6b6; line-height: 1.55; padding: 7px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a25; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; }
  .mz-prose .refs li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  /* self-assessment */
  .mz-quiz { max-width: 860px; }
  .mz-q { background: #11131a; border: 1px solid #2a2a35; border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px 18px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .mz-q .qhead { font-size: 14px; color: #fff; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .mz-q .qhead .qn { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; color: #fbbf24; font-size: 12px; margin-right: 8px; }
  .mz-opt { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 9px; padding: 9px 11px; border: 1px solid #242430; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 7px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 13px; color: #c5cbd2; }
  .mz-opt:hover { border-color: #3a3a45; background: #15171f; }
  .mz-opt input { accent-color: #67e8f9; margin-top: 2px; }
  .mz-opt.correct { border-color: #86efac; background: rgba(134,239,172,0.10); color: #d6f5e0; }
  .mz-opt.wrong { border-color: #fca5a5; background: rgba(252,165,165,0.08); color: #f5d6d6; }
  .mz-expl { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.55; margin-top: 8px; padding: 9px 11px; border-radius: 7px; display: none; }
  .mz-expl.show { display: block; }
  .mz-expl.ok { color: #86efac; background: rgba(134,239,172,0.07); border: 1px solid rgba(134,239,172,0.2); }
  .mz-expl.no { color: #fca5a5; background: rgba(252,165,165,0.07); border: 1px solid rgba(252,165,165,0.2); }
  .mz-check { background: #67e8f9; color: #06222a; border: none; border-radius: 7px; padding: 9px 18px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; cursor: pointer; margin-top: 4px; }
  .mz-check:hover { background: #97f2ff; }
  .mz-score { font-family: 'Geist Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 12px; color: #fbbf24; margin-left: 14px; font-weight: 700; }
</style>

<main class="mz-wrap">
  <a href="/aquintutor/labs" class="mz-back">
    <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" fill="none"><path d="M19 12H5M12 19l-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
    Back to Labs
  </a>
  <div class="mz-eye">Lab · Mechanical Engineering</div>
  <h1 class="mz-title">Solid mechanics, machines &amp; <em>thermal</em> cycles.</h1>
  <p class="mz-sub">Eight working benches in the IIT Virtual Labs format. Pick an experiment, read its aim, theory and procedure, then drive the live simulation — every slider re-solves the underlying engineering mathematics — and test yourself with the self-assessment.</p>

  <div class="mz-shell">
    <aside class="mz-exp-list" id="expList">
      <h4>Experiments</h4>
      <button class="mz-exp active" data-exp="beam"><span class="num">1</span><span class="nm">Shear force &amp; bending moment diagrams</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="defl"><span class="num">2</span><span class="nm">Beam deflection &amp; elastic curve</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="stress"><span class="num">3</span><span class="nm">Stress-strain &amp; material properties</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="truss"><span class="num">4</span><span class="nm">Truss analysis by method of joints</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="mohr"><span class="num">5</span><span class="nm">Mohr's circle for plane stress</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="gear"><span class="num">6</span><span class="nm">Gear trains &amp; ratios</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="thermo"><span class="num">7</span><span class="nm">Thermodynamic cycles: Otto &amp; Carnot</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="vib"><span class="num">8</span><span class="nm">Mass-spring-damper vibrations</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="fea"><span class="num">9</span><span class="nm">2D finite-element stress analysis (CST)</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="buck"><span class="num">10</span><span class="nm">Euler column buckling</span></button>
      <button class="mz-exp" data-exp="fatigue"><span class="num">11</span><span class="nm">Fatigue analysis: S-N &amp; Goodman</span></button>
    </aside>

    <div class="mz-bench">

      <!-- ================= EXPERIMENT 1: BEAM SFD/BMD ================= -->
      <section class="mz-experiment active" data-exp="beam">
        <h2 class="mz-exp-head">Shear force &amp; bending moment diagrams</h2>
        <div class="mz-exp-tag">Experiment 1 · Beam statics</div>
        <div class="mz-tabs">
          <button class="mz-tab active" data-sec="sim">Simulation</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="aim">Aim</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="theory">Theory</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="proc">Procedure</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="quiz">Self-assessment</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="ref">References</button>
        </div>

        <div class="mz-sec active" data-sec="sim">
          <div class="mz-grid">
            <aside>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Support type</h3>
                <div class="mz-seg" id="beamType">
                  <button class="on" data-t="ss">Simply supported</button>
                  <button data-t="cant">Cantilever</button>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Geometry &amp; loads</h3>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>Span L (m) <span id="b_LV">6.00</span></label><input id="b_L" type="range" min="1" max="12" step="0.1" value="6"/></div>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>Point load P (kN) <span id="b_PV">20.0</span></label><input id="b_P" type="range" min="0" max="100" step="0.5" value="20"/></div>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>Load position a (m) <span id="b_aV">3.00</span></label><input id="b_a" type="range" min="0" max="12" step="0.1" value="3"/></div>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>UDL w (kN/m) <span id="b_wV">5.0</span></label><input id="b_w" type="range" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="5"/></div>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Section &amp; material</h3>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>E (GPa) <span id="b_EV">200</span></label><input id="b_E" type="range" min="50" max="400" step="5" value="200"/></div>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>I (10^-6 m^4) <span id="b_IV">80</span></label><input id="b_I" type="range" min="5" max="500" step="5" value="80"/></div>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Results</h3>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">Reaction R_A</span><span class="mz-metric-v" id="b_RA">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">Reaction R_B</span><span class="mz-metric-v" id="b_RB">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">|V| max</span><span class="mz-metric-v amber" id="b_Vmax">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">M max</span><span class="mz-metric-v amber" id="b_Mmax">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">at x =</span><span class="mz-metric-v" id="b_Mx">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">Max deflection</span><span class="mz-metric-v green" id="b_dmax">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">Max bending stress</span><span class="mz-metric-v red" id="b_sig">—</span></div>
              </div>
            </aside>
            <div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Loaded beam</h3>
                <svg id="b_beam" class="mz-svg" viewBox="0 0 760 170" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-plots">
                <div class="mz-panel" style="margin:0;">
                  <h3>Shear force diagram · V(x) [kN]</h3>
                  <svg id="b_sfd" class="mz-svg" viewBox="0 0 380 210" preserveAspectRatio="none"></svg>
                </div>
                <div class="mz-panel" style="margin:0;">
                  <h3>Bending moment diagram · M(x) [kN·m]</h3>
                  <svg id="b_bmd" class="mz-svg" viewBox="0 0 380 210" preserveAspectRatio="none"></svg>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-panel" style="margin-top:14px;">
                <h3>Elastic curve · deflection (mm)</h3>
                <svg id="b_def" class="mz-svg" viewBox="0 0 760 150" preserveAspectRatio="none"></svg>
                <div class="mz-note">Deflection from EI&middot;y'' = M(x), integrated twice numerically with boundary conditions applied at the supports.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="aim"><div class="mz-prose"><p>To determine the support reactions of a simply-supported or cantilever beam under a point load and a uniformly distributed load (UDL), and to construct the shear force diagram (SFD) and bending moment diagram (BMD) along the span, identifying the location and magnitude of the maximum bending moment.</p></div></div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="theory"><div class="mz-prose">
          <p>For a beam in static equilibrium the sum of vertical forces and the sum of moments about any point are both zero. Reactions follow directly from these two equations for a statically-determinate beam. The shear force V(x) at a section equals the algebraic sum of transverse forces to one side; the bending moment M(x) is the sum of their moments about that section. Key relations between distributed load w, shear and moment hold along the span.</p>
          <div class="eqs">
            Sum Fy = 0,&nbsp; Sum M = 0&nbsp; (equilibrium)<br/>
            Simply supported, point load P at a:&nbsp; <b>R_B = (P&middot;a + w&middot;L&middot;L/2) / L</b><br/>
            dV/dx = -w(x)&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; dM/dx = V(x)<br/>
            M is maximum where V = 0
          </div>
          <p>The maximum bending stress on the section is sigma = M&middot;c / I, where c is the distance from the neutral axis to the extreme fibre and I the second moment of area.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="proc"><div class="mz-prose"><ol>
          <li>Select the support type (simply supported or cantilever).</li>
          <li>Set the span L, point load P and its position a, and the UDL intensity w.</li>
          <li>Read the computed support reactions R_A and R_B from the results panel.</li>
          <li>Observe the shear force diagram; note that the moment peaks where V crosses zero.</li>
          <li>Read the maximum bending moment and its location, then the resulting bending stress.</li>
          <li>Vary the load position a and watch how the diagrams and the peak moment shift.</li>
        </ol></div></div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="quiz"><div class="mz-quiz" data-quiz="beam"></div></div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="ref"><div class="mz-prose"><ul class="refs">
          <li>R. C. Hibbeler, Mechanics of Materials, 10th ed., Pearson, Ch. 6 (Bending).</li>
          <li>S. P. Timoshenko, Strength of Materials, Part I, Van Nostrand.</li>
          <li>IIT Virtual Labs — Strength of Materials, vlabs.ac.in.</li>
        </ul></div></div>
      </section>

      <!-- ================= EXPERIMENT 2: DEFLECTION ================= -->
      <section class="mz-experiment" data-exp="defl">
        <h2 class="mz-exp-head">Beam deflection &amp; elastic curve</h2>
        <div class="mz-exp-tag">Experiment 2 · Double integration</div>
        <div class="mz-tabs">
          <button class="mz-tab active" data-sec="sim">Simulation</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="aim">Aim</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="theory">Theory</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="proc">Procedure</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="quiz">Self-assessment</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="ref">References</button>
        </div>

        <div class="mz-sec active" data-sec="sim">
          <div class="mz-grid">
            <aside>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Support type</h3>
                <div class="mz-seg" id="defType">
                  <button class="on" data-t="ss">Simply supported</button>
                  <button data-t="cant">Cantilever</button>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Geometry &amp; loads</h3>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>Span L (m) <span id="d_LV">6.00</span></label><input id="d_L" type="range" min="1" max="12" step="0.1" value="6"/></div>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>Point load P (kN) <span id="d_PV">20.0</span></label><input id="d_P" type="range" min="0" max="100" step="0.5" value="20"/></div>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>Load position a (m) <span id="d_aV">3.00</span></label><input id="d_a" type="range" min="0" max="12" step="0.1" value="3"/></div>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>UDL w (kN/m) <span id="d_wV">5.0</span></label><input id="d_w" type="range" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="5"/></div>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Flexural rigidity</h3>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>E (GPa) <span id="d_EV">200</span></label><input id="d_E" type="range" min="50" max="400" step="5" value="200"/></div>
                <div class="mz-ctl"><label>I (10^-6 m^4) <span id="d_IV">80</span></label><input id="d_I" type="range" min="5" max="500" step="5" value="80"/></div>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Results</h3>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">EI</span><span class="mz-metric-v" id="d_EI">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">Max deflection</span><span class="mz-metric-v green" id="d_dmax">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">at x =</span><span class="mz-metric-v" id="d_dx">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">Max slope</span><span class="mz-metric-v amber" id="d_slope">—</span></div>
                <div class="mz-metric"><span class="mz-metric-l">Deflection / span</span><span class="mz-metric-v purple" id="d_ratio">—</span></div>
              </div>
            </aside>
            <div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Bending moment M(x) [kN·m]</h3>
                <svg id="d_bmd" class="mz-svg" viewBox="0 0 760 200" preserveAspectRatio="none"></svg>
              </div>
              <div class="mz-panel">
                <h3>Elastic curve · deflection (mm), magnified</h3>
                <svg id="d_curve" class="mz-svg" viewBox="0 0 760 230" preserveAspectRatio="none"></svg>
                <div class="mz-formula">EI&middot;y'' = M(x)&nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp; integrate once for slope theta(x), again for deflection y(x); apply <b>y(0)=y(L)=0</b> (SS) or <b>y(0)=theta(0)=0</b> (cantilever).</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="aim"><div class="mz-prose"><p>To compute the slope and deflection of a loaded beam by twice integrating the bending-moment / flexural-rigidity relation EI&middot;y'' = M(x), and to locate the point of maximum deflection and check it against the span/deflection serviceability ratio.</p></div></div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="theory"><div class="mz-prose">
          <p>The curvature of a beam is proportional to the bending moment: the governing differential equation of the elastic curve is EI&middot;d2y/dx2 = M(x). Integrating once gives the slope theta(x) = dy/dx; integrating again gives the deflection y(x). Two constants of integration are fixed by the boundary conditions. For a simply-supported beam the deflection is zero at both supports; for a cantilever the deflection and slope are both zero at the fixed end.</p>
          <div class="eqs">
            <b>EI&middot;y'' = M(x)</b><br/>
            theta(x) = (1/EI) &int; M dx&nbsp; (+ C1)<br/>
            y(x) = &int; theta dx&nbsp; (+ C2)<br/>
            SS centre point load:&nbsp; y_max = P&middot;L^3 / (48&middot;EI)<br/>
            Cantilever tip point load:&nbsp; y_max = P&middot;L^3 / (3&middot;EI)
          </div>
          <p>Here the integration is performed numerically (trapezoidal rule) over 240 stations, which reproduces the closed-form results for standard load cases.</p>
        </div></div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="proc"><div class="mz-prose"><ol>
          <li>Choose the support type and set the loads as in Experiment 1.</li>
          <li>Set the flexural rigidity by choosing the Young's modulus E and second moment of area I.</li>
          <li>The bending-moment diagram is integrated twice; read the maximum deflection and its location.</li>
          <li>Increase I (a stiffer section) and confirm the deflection falls in proportion to 1/I.</li>
          <li>Compare the deflection/span ratio with a typical serviceability limit of L/360.</li>
        </ol></div></div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="quiz"><div class="mz-quiz" data-quiz="defl"></div></div>

        <div class="mz-sec" data-sec="ref"><div class="mz-prose"><ul class="refs">
          <li>R. C. Hibbeler, Mechanics of Materials, 10th ed., Pearson, Ch. 12 (Deflection of Beams).</li>
          <li>E. P. Popov, Engineering Mechanics of Solids, Prentice Hall.</li>
          <li>IIT Virtual Labs — Strength of Materials, vlabs.ac.in.</li>
        </ul></div></div>
      </section>

      <!-- ================= EXPERIMENT 3: STRESS-STRAIN ================= -->
      <section class="mz-experiment" data-exp="stress">
        <h2 class="mz-exp-head">Stress-strain &amp; material properties</h2>
        <div class="mz-exp-tag">Experiment 3 · Tensile test</div>
        <div class="mz-tabs">
          <button class="mz-tab active" data-sec="sim">Simulation</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="aim">Aim</button>
          <button class="mz-tab" data-sec="theory">Theory</button>
