        a: 0, e: 'P_cr = pi^2·E·I/(K·L)^2; it falls with the square of the effective length.' },
      { q: 'Compared with a pinned-pinned column, a fixed-free column of the same length has an effective-length factor K of:',
        opts: ['0.5', '1', '2', '0.7'],
        a: 2, e: 'Fixed-free K = 2, so its critical load is one-quarter that of the pinned-pinned (K=1) case.' },
      { q: 'The critical buckling stress sigma_cr = pi^2·E / (K·L/r)^2 varies with slenderness as:',
        opts: ['Linearly increasing', 'Inversely with the square of slenderness', 'Independent of slenderness', 'Increasing with slenderness'],
        a: 1, e: 'sigma_cr is proportional to 1/lambda^2, so slender columns buckle at much lower stress.' },
      { q: 'A very short, stocky column under axial load is most likely to fail by:',
        opts: ['Elastic Euler buckling', 'Material yielding / crushing', 'Fatigue', 'Resonance'],
        a: 1, e: 'Below the transition slenderness the yield stress is reached before the Euler load — it crushes.' }
    ],
    fatigue: [
      { q: 'The endurance limit Se of a material is:',
